'''Normative ethics''' bridges the gap between meta-ethics (too comlex notion for what wee need here) and applied ethics. It is the attempt to arrive at practical moral standards that tell us right from wrong, and how to live moral lives. This may involve articulating the good habits that we should acquire, the duties that we should follow, or the consequences of our behavior on others.
